<br>
“Nau, just deep meditation.”<br>
<br>
“I ask, because I long to kiss you goodnight” He said<br>
<br>
“You may naut do such, not now or ever.  My body &amp; my soul are not mine to give. I gave them a long time ago to my Lord to be what I am today….”<br>
<br>
<br>
Trumpets sounded &amp; the bells of the temple ring loudly through the night.  The citizens of Free Port know a child was born in the Temple of Marr last night.<br>
<br>
Emelath &amp; Sythanas sit in their room talking in hushed whispers, the babe lay in her cradle sleeping soundly. This is the newest child of Marr. This child was born to dedicate her life to that of the Holy Knight. In this tiny baby lay all the goodness and power that her God has to give…<br>
<br>
Years pass and our baby grows to a young child. The time comes that all Holy Knights must face, the time to leave home &amp; go forth and train. With a friend in the Temple at Felwithe, Emelath &amp; Sythanas travel to the Mountains of Butcherblock, to take their only child to face her destiny.<br>
<br>
The journey through the mountain was slow, but uneventful. In the spring, the mountains were painted with bright new flowers and were utterly breathtaking. Finally, after many days travel the passage to Greater Feydark looms before them. The child runs ahead, eager to see this new land that will be her home. Emelath &amp; Sythanas follow the child slowly, allowing her the freedom she needs to see her new world.<br>
<br>
They never saw the band of elves that hit them. As they emerged from the passage to Butcherblock, fair Emelath’s body slumped to the ground as magic forces she never knew existed sang through her body. Sythanas had enough breath to call the childs name before an arrow pierced his heart &amp; he fell to his knees. The child turned at the sound of her fathers voice, and ran back to where her parents should have been… a band of elves..Koada’Dal and Fier’Dal, were circling her mother &amp; father. Her mother laying on the ground and her father on his knees so covered in blood that she did not see the arrow in his chest. She screamed and ran to her parents side.<br>
<br>
“Please, please help us!  My parents have been attacked!”<br>
<br>
As her fathers body fell, she knew she was wrong. These men were not here to help, but to kill. As the hammer fell on her back, she recognized the crest of the Holy Knights on one of men, then all was dark.<br>
<br>
I know naut how long I lay there…in the pools of blood of my parents. <br>
<br>
T’was dark when I became aware. I became aware of the cold. A chill like none I have ever known crept through my body. Just as I felt I could take no more &amp; my body would surely freeze, my mind was washed with a searing heat that made ever fiber of my being scream..and yet my body lay there quietly. Pictures flodded my brain..my parents blood, the holy crest, the smiling faces of those men, their blades covered in blood…my mind began to weep. I have never in my life felt such rage. Such pure blinding hate. A voice echoed in my brain…<br>
<br>
“Child, do you remember? Do you see? Do you feel the purity of hate?”<br>
<br>
Suddenly I knew I had a choice. I knew it as certain as I knew my name…to live or die? To live in Hate, and avenge my parents or to die and walk with them. I was so young, and the idea of being so alone was frightening, then the fire of Hate filled my blood and I knew I had but one choice. To live, and to walk in Hate. <br>
<br>
I could hear quiet praying and the distinctive sounds of a spell being cast nearby…but still I could naut open my eyes.<br>
<br>
“Child, you must say it. I must hear your choice. I have your blood, now I need your word.”<br>
<br>
“Yes, yes, I vow it. My body and my life to Hate. Let me live and let me learn to avenge those who fell”<br>
<br>
A great peace filled my broken body, suddenly I felt no pain and my body felt whole once more.<br>
<br>
