<br>
“Say good bye to your parents child. We must leave quickly, but you must say your goodbyes first”<br>
<br>
I saw where the pyre then. Rather than leave my parents bodies to the animals, she built a pyre and set them to the wind. <br>
<br>
I softly whispered goodbye. No other words, just goodbye.<br>
<br>
We quickly left the Feydark and she told me all about herself. She told me about Neriak and about growing up in Nektulos Forest. For many days we sat in the Planes just talking and waiting. She told me much of herself, and at night I dreamed. I was shown the true nature of the Teir’Dal, I was shown the beauty and the strength of the women and the pride and aggression of the men. I was shown the proper ways to talk and to act. I was shown the proper ways to attire myself, and lastly, I was shown the path I was to follow.  <br>
<br>
“Naeneori, I had another dream”<br>
<br>
“Tell me of it, Ussta Dalninil”<br>
<br>
“It told me which direction I am to go.  I must cover my self in robes as red as blood and go back to Free Port. I must journey through the tunnels and sewers to find the Dismal Rage. They will know to guide me further”<br>
<br>
“Then we must be off, gather your things, we will leave as soon as you are ready.”<br>
<br>
Within the hour, we found ourselves making our way to the mystical places in the Plane of Knowledge that would take us to Free Port. Shrouded in black robes, Naeneori guided me through the sewers to the Dismal Rage, then with a few muttered words, she was gone.<br>
<br>
I spent a long time down there training in the sewers.  Much more than I care to say, but I learned so much. By day, my new an’kin taught me the arts of the Magi, by night, Innoruuk was my an’kin and he came to my dreams &amp; taught me the ways of the dark races and the purity of Hate. Finally one night, in my dreams I was informed I was ready. Ready to venture out into the world &amp; introduce myself.<br>
<br>
Please allow me to introduce myself. I am the Pale Prophet. I am the sister of Naeneori and the Childe of Innoruuk. I am the bringer of Blood and Hate. I am Sadai.<br>
